20QM7K%2C%20which%20is%20noteworthy%20since%20last%20year's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Ftcl-qm7-qled-4k-tv-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQM7%3C%2Fa%3E%20maxed%20out%20at%2098%20inches.%20Again%2C%20with%20deal%20pricing%20in%20mind%2C%20we%20could%20be%20looking%20at%20a%20new%20benchmark%20for%20affordability%20in%20the%20midrange%20100-inch%2B%20TV%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh-end%20TV%20models%20are%20also%20getting%20extra-large%20sizes.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20Samsung%20is%20offering%20its%20flagship%20S95%20series%20OLED%20in%2083%20inches%2C%20while%20Hisense%20has%20a%20new%20premium%20116-inch%20UX%20Mini%20LED%20and%20136-inch%20Micro%20LED%20set%20for%20release%20this%20year.%20Those%20latter%20two%20models%20will%20likely%20cost%20more%20than%20%2420%2C000%2C%20but%20they're%20poised%20to%20deliver%20the%20ultimate%20big-screen%20viewing%20experience%20for%20early%20adopters%20with%20deep%20pockets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228f48e15c-5970-44e4-8025-026fbda2b275%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Brighter%20displays%5C%22%3EDisplays%20are%20getting%20brighter%2C%20but%20this%20perk%20only%20benefits%20certain%20uses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20Panasonic%20Z95B%204K%20OLED%20TVs%20on%20display%20at%20the%20CES%202025%20tech%20show.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67817ccb8951662c9f1fb036%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPansonic's%20Z95B%20will%20be%20one%20of%20the%20brightest%20OLED%20TVs%20available%20in%202025.%3Cp%3ELes%20Shu%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBrightness%20is%20a%20key%20factor%20in%20a%20TV's%20overall%20picture%20capabilities%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-tv%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20TVs%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20getting%20brighter%20every%20year.%20In%202025%2C%20companies%20are%20promising%20another%20leap%20for%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fqled-vs-oled%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQLED%20and%20OLED%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20is%20this%20bump%20in%20performance%20actually%20needed%3F%20Well%2C%20that%20depends%20on%20your%20viewing%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20brightness%20is%20beneficial%20for%20two%20primary%20reasons%3A%20it%20can%20combat%20glare%20in%20rooms%20with%20lots%20of%20light%20and%20produce%20high-dynamic%20range%20(HDR)%20images%20with%20the%20intensity%20that%20creators%20intended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20watch%20TV%20during%20the%20day%20in%20a%20room%20with%20many%20windows%2C%20you%20know%20the%20pain%20of%20fighting%20reflections.%20TVs%20with%20high%20luminance%20allow%20you%20to%20pump%20up%20the%20brightness%20setting%20to%20help%20overcome%20this.%20Some%20TVs%20can%20even%20get%20bright%20enough%20to%20suit%20outdoor%20setups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20use%20case%20where%20high%20brightness%20is%20handy%20is%20watching%20HDR%20videos.%20HDR%20is%20rarely%20used%20for%20live%20TV%2C%20so%20this%20doesn't%20impact%20most%20cable%2C%20satellite%2C%20over-the-air%2C%20or%20livestreaming%20broadcasts.%20But%20HDR%20is%20common%20in%20many%20on-demand%20streaming%20services%20and%204K%20Blu-ray%20discs.%20It%20enables%20better%20contrast%20and%20colors%20with%20more%20realistic%20highlights%2C%20like%20explosions.%20The%20brighter%20a%20TV%20can%20get%2C%20the%20more%20intense%20these%20highlights%20look.%20You%20can%20learn%20more%20in%20our%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-hdr-tv%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20HDR%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20guide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20being%20able%20to%20get%20insanely%20bright%20is%20pointless%20if%20the%20HDR%20content%20you're%20watching%20doesn't%20actually%20call%20for%20such%20high%20luminance.%20Brightness%20is%20measured%20in%20a%20unit%20called%20nits%2C%20and%20most%20HDR%20videos%20are%20mastered%20with%20a%20peak%20of%20around%201%2C000%20to%202%2C000%20nits%20in%20mind.%20A%20small%20selection%20of%20movies%20and%20shows%20are%20mastered%20for%20even%20higher%20brightness%2C%20with%2010%2C000%20being%20the%20current%20max%2C%20but%20it's%20rare%20for%20content%20to%20call%20for%20anything%20above%204%2C000%20nits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20while%20it's%20cool%20that%20we're%20getting%20new%20TVs%20that%20can%20hit%203%2C000%20nits%20and%20more%2C%20most%20of%20what%20you%20watch%20doesn't%20need%20to%20get%20that%20bright.%20We're%20starting%20to%20see%20filmmakers%20grade%20their%20movies%20with%20higher-brightness%20displays%20in%20mind%2C%20but%20such%20extreme%20capabilities%20are%20really%20only%20needed%20if%20you're%20an%20HDR%20enthusiast%20or%20you%20have%20big%20problems%20with%20glare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20still%20excited%20to%20check%20out%20these%20new%20ultra-bright%20sets%2C%20like%20Hisense's%20impressive%2010%2C000-nit%20TVs%2C%20but%20as%20a%20big%20home%20theater%20nerd%2C%20I'm%20the%20target%20audience.%20For%20most%20people%2C%20that's%20just%20overkill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22782bf14f-6479-4eb0-a135-66de66e10022%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22AI%20smart%20TV%20features%5C%22%3EBrands%20are%20touting%20smarter%20software%20with%20AI%2C%20but%20are%20these%20features%20actually%20helpful%20or%20even%20new%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221950%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20LG%20CX%20OLED%20hanging%20on%20wall%20displaying%20its%20AI%20settings.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678aae2b2fcded5e9073bd14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221463%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThough%20not%20as%20advanced%20as%20newer%20models%2C%20my%20LG%20CX%20OLED%20TV%20from%202020%20supports%20many%20AI%20optimization%20features.%3Cp%3ESteven%20Cohen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20was%20one%20major%20buzzword%20that%20appeared%20in%20nearly%20every%20TV%20brand's%20CES%20presentation%20this%20year%2C%20it%20was%20AI.%20This%20isn't%20a%20big%20surprise%20since%20AI%20features%20are%20popping%20up%20on%20various%20tech%20products%20like%20phones%20and%20laptops.%20But%20what%20might%20be%20surprising%20to%20some%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20AI-branded%20features%20on%20TVs%20are%20nothing%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI-powered%20upscaling%20processes%2C%20automatic%20picture%20adjustment%20modes%2C%20and%20other%20smart%20functions%20have%20been%20around%20for%20years.%20Many%20brands%20acknowledged%20this%20in%20their%20CES%20presentations%20by%20framing%20this%20year's%20features%20as%20the%20latest%20developments%20in%20their%20ongoing%20AI%20journeys.%20But%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20it%20does%20look%20like%20manufacturers%20are%20just%20trying%20to%20capitalize%20on%20AI's%20surging%20popularity%20by%20refreshing%20perks%20that%20have%20already%20been%20available%20and%20adding%20others%20that%20look%20a%20bit%20superfluous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Samsung%20is%20touting%20Vision%20AI%20as%20a%20big%2C%20new%20aspect%20of%20its%202025%20TV%20offerings.%20Part%20of%20Vision%20AI's%20suite%20of%20features%20includes%20AI%20picture%20and%20sound%20technologies%20that%20can%20analyze%20and%20automatically%20optimize%20performance.%20Though%20these%20processes%20are%20getting%20improvements%20for%202025%2C%20they're%20not%20new.%20Meanwhile%2C%20LG%20is%20also%20refreshing%20similar%20AI%20picture%20and%20audio%20optimizations%3A%20It%20is%20going%20so%20far%20as%20to%20rebrand%20its%20remote%20control%20as%20an%20%26quot%3BAI%20Remote%26quot%3B%20and%20rename%20the%20microphone%20button%20the%20%26quot%3BAI%20button.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20more%20substantial%20AI%20features%20are%20on%20the%20way%2C%20too.%20Samsung%20is%20adding%20a%20search%20function%20that%20lets%20you%20learn%20about%20performers%20on%20screen%20and%20a%20real-time%20translation%20function%20that%20can%20create%20subtitles.%20LG%20is%20introducing%20Voice%20ID%20that%20recognizes%20user%20voices%20to%20switch%20profiles%20and%20create%20AI-assisted%20recommendations.%20It's%20also%20using%20AI%20to%20enhance%20content%20searches%20and%20enable%20a%20ChatBot%20(first%20introduced%20in%202024%20models)%20to%20help%20with%20troubleshooting%20and%20adjusting%20settings.%20Both%20brands%20are%20launching%20generative%20image%20functions%20that%20use%20AI%20to%20create%20custom%20wallpapers%20and%20screensavers%20(something%20Amazon's%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Famazon-fire-tv-buying-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFire%20TV%20Stick%20Max%3C%2Fa%3E%20does%2C%20too).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20paper%2C%20some%20of%20these%20functions%20sound%20like%20they%20could%20be%20helpful%2C%20but%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20well%20they%20perform%2C%20and%20none%20of%20them%20sound%20like%20game%20changers%20in%20the%20smart%20TV%20space.%20Picture%20quality%20has%20gotten%20so%20good%20across%20the%20board%20that%20it's%20less%20of%20a%20differentiator%20for%20various%20TV%20brands%2C%20so%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20companies%20are%20emphasizing%20other%20features%20to%20try%20to%20stand%20out.%20It's%20great%20that%20we%20continue%20to%20get%20smarter%20smart%20TVs%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20that%20we're%20suddenly%20getting%20a%20new%20class%20of%20%26quot%3BAI%20TVs%26quot%3B%20this%20year%20is%20likely%20overblown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2F2025-tv-trends-to-watch%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737145775000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678aaaf02fcded5e9073bc56%3Fformat%3Djpe