0has%20mentioned%2C%20One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election.%20When%20elections%20happen%20repeatedly%2C%20it%20also%20impacts%20the%20government's%20ability%20to%20introduce%20reforms%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Panagariya%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20current%20situation%20actually%20provides%20a%20good%20example.%20In%20May%202024%20we%20had%20the%20parliamentary%20elections%20and%20since%20then%20we%20have%20been%20having%20one%20or%20another%20election%20every%20six%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20obviously%20denies%20the%20government%20the%20ability%20to%20bring%20major%20reforms%20because%20they%20become%20the%20bone%20of%20contention%20during%20elections%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Panagariya%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20(JPC)%20reviewing%20the%20One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election%20bill%20has%2027%20members%20from%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%2012%20from%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20(129th%20Amendment)%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20winter%20session%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20The%20bill%20would%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20state%20assemblies%2C%20and%20local%20bodies%20with%20minimum%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20its%20implementation%20will%20need%20a%20series%20of%20amendments%20to%20the%20Constitution%20that%20can%20only%20be%20done%20with%20two-thirds%20majority%20in%20parliament.%20Some%20provisions%20may%20have%20to%20be%20ratified%20by%20governments%20in%20states%20and%20Union%20Territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Opposition%20has%20voiced%20objections%2C%20with%20most%20parties%20contending%20that%20the%20bill%20would%20subvert%20the%20Constitution%20-%20an%20allegation%20the%20government%20has%20repeatedly%20refuted.%20The%20Opposition%20parties%20have%20claimed%20the%20Centre%20is%20robbing%20the%20states%20of%20the%20right%20to%20self-determination%2C%20besides%20violating%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737130860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fvktt7r68_arvind-panagariya_625x300_17_January_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F2-top-economists-to-ndtv-on-why-india-needs-1-nation-1-poll-7498178%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Finance%20Commission%20Chairman%20Arvind%20Panagariya%20in%20an%20affirmation%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20'One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election'%20explained%20that%20frequent%20elections%20do%20not%20give%20enough%20opportunities%20to%20the%20government%20to%20carry%20out%20reforms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F2-top-economists-to-ndtv-on-why-india-needs-1-nation-1-poll-7498178%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Iran%20broaches%20nuclear%20power%20plant%20agreement%20with%20Russia%20during%20talks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737130200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F25%2F01%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-vladimir-putin-masoud-pezeshkian_6802231.jpg%3F20250117141130%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firan-broaches-nuclear-power-plant-agreement-with-russia-as-they-sign-partnership-treaty-13290748%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Iran%20has%20broached%20the%20possibility%20of%20getting%20Russia's%20help%20to%20build%20a%20nuclear%20power%20plant%20during%20talks%20in%20Moscow.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firan-broaches-nuclear-power-plant-agreement-with-russia-as-they-sign-partnership-treaty-13290748%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Firan-broaches-nuclear-power-plant-agreement-with-russia-as-they-sign-partnership-treaty-13290748%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Firan-broaches-nuclear